os_brick/initiator/connectors/iscsi.py.message:
After doing the RCA, I can confirm that the right place to fix this bug is in "get_sysfs_wwn".

We just need to add a check for the dm as well.  Replacing "get_sysfs_wwn" with this code fixes the issue:

        wwid = self.get_sysfs_wwid(device_names)
        glob_str = '/dev/disk/by-id/scsi-'
        wwn_paths = glob.glob(glob_str + '*')
        # If we don't have multiple designators on page 0x83
        if wwid and glob_str + wwid in wwn_paths:
            return wwid

        dev_to_wwn = {}
        # If we have multiple designators follow the symlinks
        for wwn_path in wwn_paths:
            try:
                if os.path.islink(wwn_path) and os.stat(wwn_path):
                    path = os.path.realpath(wwn_path)
                    if path.startswith('/dev/'):
                        dev_name = path[5:]
                        wwn = wwn_path[len(glob_str):]
                        if dev_name in device_names:
                            return wwn
                        dev_to_wwn[dev_name] = wwn
            except OSError:
                continue

        mpath = self.find_sysfs_multipath_dm(device_names)
        return dev_to_wwn.get(mpath, '')

